similar to the terms of this License, but may differ in detail to
address new problems or concerns.

10.2. Effect of New Versions

Only one version of this License will be in effect at any given time.
You may choose to accept and be bound by the terms of any subsequent
version of this License that is published by the license steward by
giving notice of your acceptance to the license steward. If You do not
give such notice, then You will be bound by the terms of the version of
the License that was in effect as of the date on which You received the
Covered Software under this License.

10.3. Modified Versions

If You create software not governed by this License, and You want to
create a new license for such software, You may choose to use this
License as a starting point, provided that You: (a) change the name of
the license, removing any references to the name of the license steward
(except to the extent necessary to give notice that Your license
differs from this License); and (b) otherwise modify it in a way that
does not make it Incompatible With Secondary Licenses.

